      "text": "He wasn't even wearing shoes when he was released, and didn't live anywhere near where he was dropped off. It was an old address and his family wasn't contacted. He didn't speak English well enough to ask for the basic necessities, and the family was searching for him and reported him missing days prior. He had serious medical complications and couldn't walk without a cane. His own attorney reported him missing.\n\nThere is a simple solution for this kind of thing: bodycams.\n\nBody camera footage should clear this up and make it crystal clear. This person was EXTREMELY vulnerable and should not have been dropped off at a commercial property without any accompaniment, period.\n\nThe fact that people are on here justifying his death and absolving those who left him in that vulnerable state, is horrific. May you never be left in a blisteringly cold environment with no means to speak, see, or walk to safety, smh.",
